<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#000000"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#5C0000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Will The Thrill</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I'm making a bard for killing all kinds of monsters.  I don't plan on PvP because of my 400-500 ping lag.  <BR>My plan           Current stats<P>100 macing        85.7 macing <BR>100 tactics       86.9 tactics<BR>100 music         97.3 music<BR>100 provoke       54.3 provoke<BR>80 healing        50.6 healing<BR>80 anatomy        18 anatomy<BR>72 magery         60.7 magery   <BR>68 resist         39.4 resist<P>What do you think, I plan on killing mostly terrathons and the sort.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">sepharial</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I would raise my magic with some %´s..... I have 76% in magery... and still fizzles with lvl 6spells... and alot with lvl 7 spells.<P>Cant you skip the Anatomy and raise your magic instead? killing the monsters with your magic.<P>Good luck.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Sanek</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">You might think about fdropping the melee skills (maces/tactics) in favor of magery and meditation.  A Bard/Mage is really dangerous.<BR>I agree with the above post.  If you are going to have magery above 60, get it well above and use it with meditation as a primary offensive weapon.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Jessica</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I have a question about bard/mages and your template, what stats are you looking for, because i know that a non-GM bard will have the arrow on up and that means your dex and int up go up fasters than your str because you are also using magery, i see you having high dex high int and low str which i personally dont like but you may, like i said i'm just wondering.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Warden Dios</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">The trick for a bard/mage is to build your bard skills first,lock them, then work on strength. Your Strength building skill will be Wrestling with no tactics. Tactics is pointless if you only have the Wrestling melee skill. Your mainly interested in avoiding being disrupted not inflicting damage. My Bard/Mage has stats of str/dex/int = 95/30/100 using this method. He is GM Provoke/music/magery/wrestling...</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">alvinleong</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Warden Dios, that was (still is) exactly my plan too.  I've recently GMed music/provoke, and as expected my stats went to pot.. Str/Dex/Int was 39/100/86.. ouch.  So I macroed herding to regain Str.  I overdid it, now Str/Dex/Int is 93/95/37.. ouch :P<P>What would you suggest?  My current idea is to work on EI (I'm at 91.4) to raise Int.  When I finally get Int back up to 50, I'll wrestle (currently 98.9) summoned elementals whilst working on EI as well.. help?<P>------------------<BR>Alvin the Lonely, of Europa<BR>http://www.geocities.com/yosemite/1230<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Warden Dios</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">alvinleong,<BR>Ive found that Int is really tough to build but as long as you use only magery skills (magery, ei,med) and strength skills your str and int will go up and your dex will go down. Its just slow.  If you have some points to spare you could either try Spirit Speak to get your Int back up then mark it Down when you are finished.<BR>When I finished  Gm'ing in Music, Provoke and  Magery my stats were a pitiful str/dex/int = 49/76/100. Luckily for me the Skill Lock patch just went into production so I Locked Barding skills , Wrestling up, Tactics Down and proceded to GM in Wrestling on my Polar bears. The bad part about stat gain at the Stat Cap is that gains are easy to control buy what skills you use but loses (due to gains) are uncontrollable.  In fact they appear to be random.  Anyways, when I Gm'd in Wrestling my stats were something like 95/53/77.  As you can see I lost an equal amount of int as i did dex.  It took lots more wrestling and Magery use after this for my skills to finally settle down at 95/30/100 and I'm still trying to get my dex down to 25.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Ox</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">naaa<BR> melee skills do nothing if you want to kill all kinds of monsters<P>you should go for the classic bard/mage<P>100 provocation<BR>100 musicianship<BR>100 magery<BR>100 evaluate intelligence<BR>100 meditation<BR>100 resisting spells<BR>100 (i prefer peacemake which is a nice choice in sticky situations)<P>------------------<BR>when will bards on siege get a break?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Ox</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">But.....<P>being a bard is .... an adventure itself and you shouldent let anyone steer you when making your bard<P></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
